      {
        "id": 2766909,
        "name": "Dennis Atick",
        "username": "Dennis_Atick",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_atick/{size}/429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-12-06T17:24:42.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I don\u2019t own a lot of Cornas, I have enough good stuff to scratch the itch when it calls. I had planned all afternoon to open the 2011 Voge Chailles, accidentally pulled this one and was moving too quick and did not realize I had opened the Clape until I was pouring it into the decanter. Oops.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=1507739&amp;iNote=8040708\"><strong>2011 Domaine Auguste Clape Cornas</strong></a> <em>- France, Rh\u00f4ne, Northern Rh\u00f4ne, Cornas (12/5/2019)</em><br>\nI\u2019m not seeing the same wine as these reviews before mine in CT. My comment would be DO NOT OPEN THIS WINE NOW. It is closed up tight. Hard as nails. Even with 60 minutes in decanter\u2026Maybe I just like my wines with more age. Primary, shiny fruit and hardcore structure. So tight, it doesn\u2019t even say Northern Rhone to me right now. More patience is needed. Or maybe '11 just isn\u2019t that special.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
