        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/ba9def/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-02-10T02:37:53.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Opened a 2011 Clape CdR tonight and it was drinking great. More earthy than when it was younger but still get that \u201ccrushed fruit over rocks\u201d I like so much from these wines. I find these to have a lot of the same calling cards as the Cornas, without the tannin. Obviously not the same highs, but a very good alternative when you don\u2019t have a bunch of older bottles of the Cornas lying around</p>",
