        "username": "Ramon_C",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ramon_c/{size}/1372_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-02-10T12:59:01.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Sorry to hear about the unforeseen error with the \u201811 Clape Cornas.  These wines, especially by a great producer, are usually very tough to drink within their first 20 years.  But they\u2019ll be very nice later on.</p>\n<p>Also, hard to compare with the similar vintage Saint Joseph in terms of same stage drinkability.</p>",
